{
  "stem": "1343.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went, and to tell you the truth, at that time, I did not have much faith in God.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After this aunt episode, then I said, oh, I don't want to have anything to do.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Whatever I believed is-- is gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If there is a God, he's impotent or very cruel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I don't want anything to do with it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And yet, when I went down to Gyongyos, I said, about me, I do whatever I want, but I have to go to the shul and say a Kaddish for my parents because that, I [? wanted ?] So I wanted to go to the shul.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the orthodox shul in Gyongyos was on a little hill.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were some 12, 14 steps to go up on the hill.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as I opened the door to the shul, I am faced with the behinds of horses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These Russian son of a guns, they did it on purpose to denigrate any-- but they did that with the churches, too, I have to admit.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you know how uncomfortable to schlep up horses on a hill, on steps?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they did it just to the show how much think-- so I went into that shul.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[SIGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And where the sacred Torahs used to be kept, there was a huge manure-- bunch of manure.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Horses were defecating, urinating where my Rabbi Yungrais used to daven.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had enough of it there, and I said, never ever again I want to believe in God because there isn't any.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can't help it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When the children come, what can you tell them?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I first came here, one of the reasons that I changed my name was that I wanted to get away from it all.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in Gyongyos, I came back.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
